abstract: Twelve days. Nine sprawling performances. Two cities. One Kirill Petrenko, whose conducting is “molten, combustible, an eruption of color.”
snippet: Twelve days. Nine sprawling performances. Two cities. One Kirill Petrenko, whose conducting is “molten, combustible, an eruption of color.”
lead_paragraph: BAYREUTH, Germany — The word we still use is “pilgrimage,” for, as Mark Twain put it back in 1891, “a pilgrimage is what it is.” Each summer, tens of thousands of true believers shuffle their way up a small green hill to the north of this German town, toward the shrine that Richard Wagner built to his dramas and dreams. Some are seasoned followers; some, like me this year, are practicing their devotions for the first time.

headline_main: Trump Tower Meeting, Drone Attack, Indonesia: Your Monday Briefing

abstract: Australia’s race commissioner exited office with an indictment of race-baiting commentators and politicians. Here are excerpts from his speech, annotated.
snippet: Australia’s race commissioner exited office with an indictment of race-baiting commentators and politicians. Here are excerpts from his speech, annotated.
lead_paragraph: Tim Soutphommasane, Australia’s race discrimination commissioner, will end his five-year term this month and issued a blistering assessment on Monday of the country’s politics and its commitment to racial equality.

abstract: Red Sox pitcher Rick Porcello allowed one hit Friday night in a game that included warnings to both benches in the first inning.
snippet: Red Sox pitcher Rick Porcello allowed one hit Friday night in a game that included warnings to both benches in the first inning.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Luis Severino delivered a message with his first pitch on Friday night — a fastball under Mookie Betts’s chin, which sent Betts sprawling into the dirt, the Fenway Park crowd into a frenzy and Red Sox Manager Alex Cora into a tizzy.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo is urging Asian allies to keep pressuring North Korea with economic sanctions.
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo is urging Asian allies to keep pressuring North Korea with economic sanctions.
lead_paragraph: SINGAPORE — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo expressed growing exasperation with North Korea on Friday, accusing its government of refusing to respect a promise to President Trump to stop, or even slow, Pyongyang’s nuclear weapons program.
